cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the relevance of search engine results, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The study also involves user behavior and evaluation, which can be related to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The use of binary and graded relevance judgments can be linked to Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Deep Learning (cs.DL) techniques. Finally, the study involves the assessment of content quality, which can be related to Cybersecurity (cs.CR).
